{"id":221619032,"title":"Asynchronous Distributed Learning of Topic Models.","authors":["Arthur U. Asuncion","Padhraic Smyth","Max Welling"],"_abstract":"ABSTRACT Distributed learning is a problem of fundamental interest in machine learning and cognitive science. In this paper, we present asynchronous distributed learning al- gorithms for two well-known unsupervised learning frameworks: Latent Dirichlet Allocation (LDA) and Hierarchical Dirichlet Processes (HDP). In the proposed approach, the data are distributed across P processors, and processors indepen- dently perform Gibbs sampling on their local data and communicate their infor- mation in a local asynchronous manner with other processors. We demonstrate that our asynchronous algorithms are able to learn global topic models that are statistically as accurate as those learned by the standard L DA and HDP samplers, but with significant improvements in computation time and me mory. We show speedup results on a 730-million-word text corpus using 32 processors, and we provide perplexity results for up to 1500 virtual processor s. As a stepping stone in the development of asynchronous HDP, a parallel HDP sampler is also introduced.","cited_in":[{"id":280221142,"url":"https://www.researchgate.net/publication/280221142_Incremental_Variational_Inference_for_Latent_Dirichlet_Allocation"},{"id":269722321,"url":"https://www.researchgate.net/publication/269722321_A_Scalable_Asynchronous_Distributed_Algorithm_for_Topic_Modeling"},{"id":268155582,"url":"https://www.researchgate.net/publication/268155582_Model-Parallel_Inference_for_Big_Topic_Models"},{"id":224907478,"url":"https://www.researchgate.net/publication/224907478_Dynamic_Multi-Relational_Chinese_Restaurant_Process_for_AnalyzingInfluences_on_Users_in_Social_Media"},{"id":224216843,"url":"https://www.researchgate.net/publication/224216843_Understanding_Errors_in_Approximate_Distributed_Latent_Dirichlet_Allocation"},{"id":254008792,"url":"https://www.researchgate.net/p